Contains:
1.Om Shanti from November 16, 1992 - 22 minutes
&quot;Freedom, liberation, enlightenment, moksha.&quot;
You don't need to give shine to the mirror or hold a light up to the Sun. This Peace, this Beauty, this Consciousness...with this Light you will see your Eternal Face.

2.Om Shanti from January 9, 1993 - during the Jayanti Celebration in celebration of Sri Ramana Maharshi - 16 minutes - &quot;I am with you wherever you are.&quot;
Papaji speaks about meeting his teacher and his experiences with Sri Ramana Maharshi. This marks the end of all searching for Papaji after he meets a man who has seen God.

3.Om Shanti from January 11, 1993 - 7 minutes
&quot;Introduce yourself to this Moment.&quot;
Papaji challenges you to get intimately acquainted with this moment.

4.Om Shanti from January 22, 1993 - 5 minutes
&quot;Who are you?&quot;
Papaji tells you in this instant to open yourself to the Self. In this very instant - not past, not future, not even present.

5.Om Shanti from March 23, 1993 - 2 minutes
&quot;So this is the teaching...you don't need any teaching.&quot;
If you empty your mind, you will encounter no mind and through no mind you will understand the Source of no mind.

6.Om Shanti from April 15, 1993 - 26 minutes
&quot;What's going on here in Lucknow&quot;
The first Satsang following Papaji's trip to Kathmandu after his meetings with various Rimpoches and other Bhuddhist teachers.
This talk is a good introduction to Papaji's Satsangs.
